WEBVTT

00:02.878 --> 00:03.962
It's her first day.

00:03.962 --> 00:05.964
Welcome to Theranos.

00:05.964 --> 00:07.549
- Here, put it on the camera
on your computer.

00:07.549 --> 00:08.634
Why?

00:08.634 --> 00:10.010
So they can't watch you.

00:10.010 --> 00:13.931
- If Ian had testified, it would have
invalidated Theranos' patents.

00:13.931 --> 00:16.642
- For a story like this, I really need
someone with firsthand knowledge.

00:16.642 --> 00:18.602
<i>They must be running
everything on the Siemens machines</i>

00:18.602 --> 00:19.645
<i>to get around the regulators.</i>

00:19.645 --> 00:20.979
- Do you really think
she'd let that happen?

00:20.979 --> 00:23.482
- Dude, she is the CEO.
She knows what's going on.

00:23.482 --> 00:25.359
- Are you running
the Edison proficiency tests

00:25.359 --> 00:26.360
on Siemens machines?

00:26.360 --> 00:28.654
- You have no idea
what you're talking about.

00:28.654 --> 00:32.406
- You believe Theranos
is lying to regulators?

00:32.406 --> 00:34.618
- Yeah, that's why we need you
to start asking questions.

00:34.618 --> 00:36.203
No, I won't.

00:36.203 --> 00:37.663
I'm ready for your questions now.

00:37.663 --> 00:40.165
How is Theranos defrauding Walgreens?

00:40.165 --> 00:42.209
<i>Yeah, hello.</i>

00:42.209 --> 00:43.836
TYLER SCHULTZ:
Uh, John Carreyrou?

00:43.836 --> 00:45.420
This is Tyler Schultz.

00:48.924 --> 00:51.134
You founded
this company 12 years ago, right?

00:52.261 --> 00:53.971
Tell them how old you were.

00:53.971 --> 00:55.639
-I was 19.

00:57.516 --> 00:58.600
- So--

01:02.729 --> 01:04.773
Don't worry about the future,
we're in good hands.

01:06.149 --> 01:09.111
♪

01:09.111 --> 01:11.947
♪

02:09.171 --> 02:14.843
- I look back on this
brilliant young woman's, uh, vision,

02:14.843 --> 02:18.597
and I think to myself,
how in God's name at 19

02:18.597 --> 02:22.643
was she able to convince some
of the leading professors in America,

02:22.643 --> 02:26.980
uh, let alone her parents,
to give her all her tuition money

02:26.980 --> 02:28.857
to go and say, "I got an idea.

02:29.525 --> 02:30.901
I'm going to start a company."

02:59.680 --> 03:01.974
- So the Theranos report
for the patient came back

03:01.974 --> 03:04.142
showing an abnormally high TSH value.

03:05.143 --> 03:07.312
- But the patient was already taking
thyroid medication

03:07.312 --> 03:09.356
- to lower that value?
- Precisely.

03:09.356 --> 03:12.860
And the Theranos results indicated
the medication wasn't working.

03:13.277 --> 03:14.361
Was Theranos correct?

03:14.903 --> 03:17.155
This patient was pregnant, okay.

03:17.614 --> 03:20.868
Increasing her dosage would have made
her thyroid hormone levels so high,

03:20.868 --> 03:22.828
it would have put her pregnancy at risk.

03:24.580 --> 03:26.164
Would you go on the record with this?

03:27.457 --> 03:28.834
- Abso-fucking-lutely.

03:30.669 --> 03:33.589
- I tracked down a patient
who spent Thanksgiving in the ER

03:33.589 --> 03:36.133
because a Theranos test
told her incorrectly

03:36.133 --> 03:37.676
- she was having a stroke.
- Mm.

03:37.676 --> 03:39.428
Thousands of dollars in medical bills.

03:39.428 --> 03:41.305
I spoke with a cancer survivor,

03:41.305 --> 03:43.557
took a Theranos test,
thought her cancer had come back.

03:43.557 --> 03:44.600
Jesus.

03:44.600 --> 03:47.352
I have three doctors on the record.

03:47.352 --> 03:48.854
I have the Mark Roessler emails.

03:48.854 --> 03:50.063
He sent you those?

03:50.063 --> 03:51.773
No, not yet, but he should shortly.

03:51.773 --> 03:53.233
From what he describes,
they're pretty damning.

03:53.233 --> 03:55.485
I've got Gardner and Gibbons on the record

03:55.485 --> 03:57.613
and Tyler Schultz on background.

03:57.613 --> 03:59.781
Wait, wait, uh, back up. Tyler who?

03:59.781 --> 04:01.533
- This kid worked in the labs
with Erika Cheung.

04:01.533 --> 04:03.577
He's George Schultz's grandson.

04:03.577 --> 04:04.620
Huh.

04:05.162 --> 04:06.997
Does Schultz know his grandson
is talking to us?

04:06.997 --> 04:09.208
- Oh no. And I have to make sure
he doesn't.

04:09.208 --> 04:10.626
Yeah, no shit.

04:11.668 --> 04:13.462
- It smells really good.
- Mm-hmm.

04:13.462 --> 04:15.130
- Can I have the crackers?
- Nope.

04:15.130 --> 04:17.925
So we ought to be thankful
that Elizabeth Holmes wasn't running

04:17.925 --> 04:19.009
the USSR in the '80s.

04:19.009 --> 04:20.093
Yeah.

04:20.093 --> 04:22.012
- Okay, so you do know
what I'm going to ask--

04:22.012 --> 04:23.388
She's not going to talk to me, Judith.

04:23.388 --> 04:25.933
I'm the only reporter in America
she will not give an interview to.

04:25.933 --> 04:27.684
- Doesn't matter.
We have to be able to say

04:27.684 --> 04:30.354
we made every effort
to allow Theranos to respond.

04:30.354 --> 04:31.939
I sent them a list of questions.

04:31.939 --> 04:34.399
- Okay.
- I am a little bit worried

04:34.399 --> 04:36.109
they're going to come after my sources.

04:36.109 --> 04:37.986
They've got David Boies representing them.

04:37.986 --> 04:39.321
Yeah, fuck that.

04:39.321 --> 04:42.616
Whatever they throw at us,
we can handle it.

04:43.492 --> 04:47.204
But maybe also call Mark Roessler
and have him hurry up with those e-mails.

05:01.635 --> 05:04.888
♪

05:24.533 --> 05:27.953
♪

05:27.953 --> 05:30.205
♪

05:37.629 --> 05:40.048
♪

05:49.349 --> 05:51.935
Wall Street Journal
<i>is doing an article about Theranos,</i>

05:51.935 --> 05:53.270
and it is, um--

05:54.146 --> 05:56.064
I don't think it's going to be positive.

05:56.064 --> 05:59.067
Uh, here are some questions they sent over

05:59.067 --> 06:02.029
that they would like you to, uh,

06:02.029 --> 06:05.782
to an-- to answer
as soon as you possibly can--

06:05.782 --> 06:07.868
- Yo, I've been trying
to get ahold of you.

06:08.368 --> 06:10.746
Mark just downloaded, like,
hundreds of work e-mails

06:10.746 --> 06:13.123
to his personal drive,
and now he's headed out of the building.

06:13.123 --> 06:15.000
- Mark?
- Yeah.

06:18.253 --> 06:19.505
Where is Mark?

06:20.130 --> 06:21.298
Mark!

06:21.298 --> 06:22.257
What's he going to do to him?

06:22.257 --> 06:23.467
Sunny!

06:23.467 --> 06:24.718
Mark!

06:25.427 --> 06:28.472
♪

06:28.472 --> 06:31.725
♪

06:33.060 --> 06:35.562
Mark, I will sue your ass!

06:35.562 --> 06:39.149
Delete those emails!
We have an NDA, Mark.

06:39.149 --> 06:41.109
- These questions are ridiculous.
- And sloppy.

06:41.109 --> 06:42.819
Yeah, he's not a good writer.

06:42.819 --> 06:44.863
- I, I tried reading
his Medicare thing the other night.

06:44.863 --> 06:46.073
It, like, sucked.

06:46.073 --> 06:48.242
- I mean, I mean,
he should be more careful.

06:48.242 --> 06:50.619
These questions make it obvious
who his sources are.

06:52.829 --> 06:54.039
You know who his sources are?

06:54.039 --> 06:55.791
- Yes, of course.
- We believe we do.

06:55.791 --> 06:57.626
- We've narrowed it down.
Thank you, Peter.

06:57.626 --> 06:58.836
He's spoken to Rochelle Gibbons.

06:58.836 --> 07:00.587
Who we should sue for defamation.

07:00.587 --> 07:03.090
And some doctors
and patients in Arizona,

07:03.090 --> 07:04.925
which violates
doctor-patient confidentiality.

07:04.925 --> 07:08.053
- And those questions regarding
the particulars of the Normandy lab,

07:08.053 --> 07:09.680
those are, that's coming from Erika.

07:09.680 --> 07:12.516
- Yeah. Erika Cheung,
Tyler Schultz, Mark Roessler.

07:12.516 --> 07:14.309
Who all signed NDAs.

07:14.309 --> 07:16.812
- That's right. And who are young
and disgruntled.

07:16.812 --> 07:18.981
- Very fucking disgruntled.
- All three left after disagreements.

07:18.981 --> 07:21.275
- But they expect us to answer
these questions,

07:21.275 --> 07:22.734
like, I, I--

07:23.318 --> 07:26.655
This, this whole thing that we have
to respond to liars?

07:27.114 --> 07:28.073
That's ridiculous.

07:29.658 --> 07:31.326
And all these legal elements,

07:31.326 --> 07:33.328
we have to get, we have to get ahead
of all of them now.

07:33.328 --> 07:35.122
SUNNY:
Extremely serious legal implications.

07:35.122 --> 07:37.541
Like, Tyler basically violated
and shared our trade secrets.

07:37.541 --> 07:38.542
Literally.

07:38.542 --> 07:40.419
SUNNY:
Violating trade secrets is not okay.

07:40.419 --> 07:41.461
We want to sue everyone.

07:42.713 --> 07:43.797
Everyone?

07:43.797 --> 07:45.549
- We want to nail this motherfucker.
- Yeah.

07:51.638 --> 07:52.806
Well...

07:53.974 --> 07:56.643
I respect the integrity of journalism.

07:57.269 --> 07:58.854
I represent the <i>New York Times.</i>

07:59.563 --> 08:02.691
But there are tools and tactics available

08:02.691 --> 08:06.945
that we can use to try
and suppress negative stories.

08:06.945 --> 08:09.239
And we can remind them of the consequences

08:09.239 --> 08:11.158
of breaking their NDAs.

08:11.158 --> 08:12.284
Linda will help me with that.

08:13.118 --> 08:15.787
And then, of course,
we can question their credibility.

08:16.330 --> 08:18.582
If these are the kind of people
that break their NDAs,

08:18.582 --> 08:20.250
how can we trust anything they say?

08:20.709 --> 08:22.294
Good. Yeah. Good.

08:22.294 --> 08:25.797
♪

08:25.797 --> 08:28.133
♪

08:28.133 --> 08:31.428
♪

08:34.056 --> 08:35.182
Hey, Tiger.

08:37.726 --> 08:38.977
Are you home?

08:39.937 --> 08:41.063
I'm back.

08:41.688 --> 08:43.190
I got to tell you something.

08:44.233 --> 08:45.359
Come find me.

08:49.488 --> 08:52.324
This house is too big. I can't.

08:56.036 --> 08:56.995
Here.

08:58.664 --> 09:02.042
- I met Rupert Murdoch tonight
at the thing.

09:15.180 --> 09:16.265
I'm sorry.

09:18.141 --> 09:19.226
You started it.

09:24.064 --> 09:26.942
- Rupert Murdoch invited me
to his ranch tonight.

09:30.487 --> 09:32.614
God, I am so happy.

09:35.492 --> 09:38.287
- I'm going to Arizona tomorrow
to talk to the doctors.

09:38.287 --> 09:39.454
I don't care

09:40.080 --> 09:41.623
that Boies has a strategy.

09:43.625 --> 09:45.419
I want to talk to them face-to-face.

09:47.129 --> 09:50.132
End this smear campaign,
take out his sources.

09:51.133 --> 09:52.926
Cut this off at the legs one by one.

09:53.343 --> 09:55.470
We can turn this around.

10:00.893 --> 10:02.436
I'm not here to scare you.

10:04.855 --> 10:06.231
I'm simply asking you,

10:07.649 --> 10:10.402
does your practice rely on online reviews?

10:14.239 --> 10:16.408
It would hurt your practice
if your patients knew

10:16.408 --> 10:19.536
you shared their confidential
health information

10:20.037 --> 10:21.246
with a reporter.

10:22.164 --> 10:23.248
Right?

10:26.043 --> 10:27.628
But if you sign that document,

10:29.713 --> 10:31.048
all this goes away.

10:33.467 --> 10:37.221
- I've always believed
that we are here on this Earth

10:37.804 --> 10:40.140
to make a difference in the world.

10:41.141 --> 10:44.853
So when I found what I felt like
I was born to do,

10:45.437 --> 10:48.190
which is help and try to contribute

10:48.190 --> 10:51.235
to, to solving a problem--

10:51.235 --> 10:53.070
- Hello.
<i>I'm being followed, John.</i>

10:53.070 --> 10:55.531
Like, everywhere I go,
there's someone watching me.

10:55.531 --> 10:57.449
- Who's watching you?
<i>- I, I don't know,</i>

10:57.449 --> 10:58.659
but I'm not making it up.

10:58.659 --> 11:01.328
It's not safe in my house.
I'm, I'm in the car.

11:01.328 --> 11:03.163
I'm using the Wi-Fi in my car.

11:03.163 --> 11:05.832
I believe that on a human level,

11:05.832 --> 11:08.168
<i>there's not much else that matters.</i>

11:08.669 --> 11:10.879
CHARLIE ROSE:
<i>Access to more data will save more lives.</i>

11:11.338 --> 11:15.968
<i>Yeah, when,
you know, in saving lives...</i>

11:21.056 --> 11:23.350
when you're talking
about someone you love,

11:23.350 --> 11:25.018
you'd do anything, right?

11:26.061 --> 11:27.604
-<i>I get these phone calls...</i>
- Mark. Mark.

11:27.604 --> 11:30.691
from, from Sunny
and their goddamn lawyers,

11:30.691 --> 11:31.608
they're threatening me--

11:31.608 --> 11:33.151
- I told you they were going
to come after you.

11:33.151 --> 11:34.528
<i>...these massive lawsuits.</i>

11:37.781 --> 11:40.784
♪

11:40.784 --> 11:45.289
♪

11:50.419 --> 11:54.923
Has anybody challenged
the science of what you do?

11:55.424 --> 11:58.010
I hired a lawyer,
a very good lawyer.

11:58.552 --> 12:02.139
But he found out they had
David Boies on, on their side,

12:02.139 --> 12:04.975
and he told me to delete
the emails immediately.

12:04.975 --> 12:06.310
Don't delete the emails, Mark.

12:06.310 --> 12:07.895
What you're doing is too important.

12:07.895 --> 12:11.064
- I don't know.
I, I, I don't know if I can do this.

12:11.064 --> 12:13.525
Are there people
who raise questions and say,

12:14.443 --> 12:16.820
you know, why doesn't she
show us all this?

12:16.820 --> 12:20.073
Because we'd feel more comfortable
with the results.

12:20.073 --> 12:22.284
ELIZABETH:
The major lab companies, yeah.

12:22.284 --> 12:25.913
Help me understand
what it is they're asking

12:25.913 --> 12:28.207
and what your answer is to them.

12:30.417 --> 12:32.961
- I know it's scary right now--
- They can bankrupt me.

12:32.961 --> 12:35.631
- But they wouldn't make it scary
if they weren't scared.

12:35.631 --> 12:37.966
And they're scared because they know

12:37.966 --> 12:40.052
that they're wrong and you're right.

12:40.052 --> 12:42.304
<i>What you're doing is going to save lives.</i>

12:42.304 --> 12:43.472
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.

12:43.472 --> 12:46.225
- Mark, you did this because
you're going to save people.

12:46.225 --> 12:47.392
<i>Uh-huh. Yeah.</i>

12:47.392 --> 12:49.186
Yeah, yeah, yeah. No, you're right.

12:50.312 --> 12:51.772
<i>So you'll send me those emails?</i>

12:52.356 --> 12:53.440
Yeah, yeah.

12:57.653 --> 12:58.612
Mark?

13:02.074 --> 13:03.075
<i>Mark?</i>

13:09.831 --> 13:10.791
Mark.

13:11.875 --> 13:13.377
MARK:
<i>Sorry, John, I'm sorry.</i>

13:18.006 --> 13:19.341
JOHN:
<i>The Roessler emails are gone.</i>

13:19.341 --> 13:21.176
Most of the Arizona doctors are gone.

13:21.176 --> 13:23.846
If they manage to sway Tyler,
I, I do not have a story.

13:23.846 --> 13:26.849
Well, then get Tyler on the phone.

13:26.849 --> 13:29.518
- I've tried to get Tyler on the phone.
He doesn't pick up.

13:29.518 --> 13:32.479
- Well, try again.
- I have tried trying again.

13:32.479 --> 13:35.357
- Well, have you tried
texting, emailing...

13:35.357 --> 13:36.942
- I have tried everything.
- ...sending him flowers?

13:36.942 --> 13:38.527
Well, then you're just going
to have to wait.

13:38.527 --> 13:40.988
Wait. Great.

13:40.988 --> 13:42.865
I will just wait.

13:42.865 --> 13:45.826
That is really helpful, Judith. Thank you.

13:49.580 --> 13:51.665
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
It's okay.

13:53.125 --> 13:55.544
- This is really taking a toll on me.
- I can see that.

13:59.423 --> 14:01.216
You just can't lose Tyler.

14:07.014 --> 14:11.018
♪

14:20.110 --> 14:21.445
Grandpa, what's up?

14:22.946 --> 14:25.866
I'm not sure why Elizabeth thinks that

14:26.867 --> 14:28.994
I was the one who spoke to some,

14:30.621 --> 14:33.999
- some reporter.
- Did you... Tyler?

14:34.833 --> 14:36.293
Because if you did,

14:36.293 --> 14:37.920
you're in danger of being sued.

14:39.546 --> 14:40.964
Just tell me.

14:41.840 --> 14:43.050
We're family.

14:45.010 --> 14:46.678
Did you speak to the reporter?

14:48.472 --> 14:49.473
No.

14:50.307 --> 14:52.226
- No.
- Oh, that's good.

14:53.060 --> 14:54.478
GEORGE SCHULTZ:
So then,

14:56.063 --> 14:57.731
all you have to do

14:58.232 --> 15:00.692
is sign a new non-disclosure agreement.

15:01.777 --> 15:02.736
What?

15:03.487 --> 15:04.613
Linda!

15:04.613 --> 15:06.406
- Is someone here?
- George.

15:06.406 --> 15:07.449
Is there someone upstairs?

15:07.449 --> 15:10.744
- A lawyer from Theranos brought
the document for you to sign.

15:10.744 --> 15:11.787
You told me to come over and talk.

15:11.787 --> 15:12.955
You didn't tell me
I have to sign anything.

15:12.955 --> 15:13.664
Linda.

15:16.333 --> 15:17.417
Linda!

15:18.043 --> 15:18.877
Okay.

15:20.003 --> 15:21.171
Okay.

15:21.171 --> 15:23.966
- This matter is more urgent
than you realize.

15:27.511 --> 15:29.555
Hi. Hi, Tyler.

15:29.555 --> 15:31.890
I have some documents
you're going to need to sign.

15:31.890 --> 15:34.184
Okay, here's the restraining order.

15:34.184 --> 15:35.477
BOTH:
A restraining order?

15:35.477 --> 15:36.979
Are you fucking serious?

15:36.979 --> 15:38.313
No, that's wrong.

15:38.313 --> 15:41.400
Elizabeth said he was going
to sign a nondisclosure agreement.

15:41.400 --> 15:43.902
- This is a letter from Theranos
stating that they believe

15:43.902 --> 15:46.780
that you have violated
your confidentiality obligations.

15:46.780 --> 15:48.448
- This is not what
Elizabeth said was going--

15:48.448 --> 15:50.284
- That they're preparing to file
a lawsuit against you.

15:50.284 --> 15:52.619
- Is this coming from Sunny?
- I didn't speak to the reporter.

15:52.619 --> 15:54.580
- Would you be willing to sign
an affidavit to that effect?

15:54.580 --> 15:57.124
Would you be willing to name
the people who did in fact speak

15:57.124 --> 15:58.292
to <i>The Wall Street Journal?</i>

15:58.292 --> 15:59.835
My grandson is not a rat.

15:59.835 --> 16:01.837
- George, why don't you let me
take it from here?

16:01.837 --> 16:05.757
- Like hell I will.
You, into the study now.

16:05.757 --> 16:07.176
Tyler, you stay here.

16:07.176 --> 16:09.720
We're going to settle this with decorum.

16:10.429 --> 16:11.430
Sit down.

16:14.183 --> 16:16.018
You won't be talking to Tyler directly.

16:16.977 --> 16:18.979
You'll be using me as an intermediary.

16:20.731 --> 16:22.191
Is this really necessary?

16:22.191 --> 16:24.484
It was good enough for Gorbachev,

16:24.484 --> 16:26.236
and it will be good enough for you.

16:28.238 --> 16:30.199
♪

16:34.494 --> 16:36.705
How are you doing?
Are you hungry?

16:37.206 --> 16:39.625
Charlotte, can we have
some crackers in here?

16:40.959 --> 16:42.544
Can you just tell her not to sue me?

16:43.295 --> 16:45.047
We're taking the lawsuit off the table.

16:45.047 --> 16:46.215
We can't do that.

16:46.215 --> 16:47.633
Then he won't be signing.

16:47.633 --> 16:48.967
That's a red line?

16:53.514 --> 16:57.392
- Good news, they're agreeing
not to sue you for two years.

16:57.392 --> 16:59.102
So they're going to sue me in two years?

16:59.102 --> 17:02.022
- Jesus Christ, George,
this is your grandson.

17:07.736 --> 17:10.656
LINDA:
Fine, we will agree not to sue.

17:10.656 --> 17:12.032
And you'll put that in writing.

17:12.032 --> 17:13.659
Yes, we'll draft it up right now.

17:13.659 --> 17:15.953
But if we do, he'll sign?

17:15.953 --> 17:19.164
No, I, I won't sign it.

17:19.164 --> 17:21.750
- Those were your terms.
- Well, my terms have changed.

17:21.750 --> 17:22.835
Why?

17:23.961 --> 17:25.629
Because you did speak to a reporter.

17:26.630 --> 17:28.090
Because if you did

17:28.090 --> 17:30.968
and you sign these documents,
you'll be perjuring yourself.

17:30.968 --> 17:32.970
- Okay.
- What are you doing here?

17:32.970 --> 17:37.140
- Tyler, I've modified the documents
to meet your demands.

17:37.140 --> 17:38.308
Now sign.

17:39.601 --> 17:42.729
♪

17:44.898 --> 17:46.441
George...

17:46.441 --> 17:48.777
why don't you fax
the documents to your lawyer

17:48.777 --> 17:50.988
and see what he thinks Taylor should do?

18:17.347 --> 18:19.975
Tyler, your mom's on the phone.

18:21.768 --> 18:23.604
If you'd like, you can take it upstairs.

18:29.818 --> 18:31.904
- Why did my mom call here?
Is everything okay?

18:36.366 --> 18:39.578
- Tyler, I know you spoke
with the reporter.

18:41.705 --> 18:42.664
- No, I--

18:43.498 --> 18:44.791
I didn't.

18:46.043 --> 18:49.004
- I didn't, I--
- This is our attorney on the phone.

18:52.341 --> 18:54.510
Tell him your situation.

18:54.510 --> 18:55.844
He can help you.

18:56.512 --> 18:57.596
- I'm--

19:04.311 --> 19:07.314
♪

19:17.783 --> 19:19.660
GEORGE:
My lawyer says he shouldn't sign.

19:19.660 --> 19:20.869
Why?

19:21.870 --> 19:24.581
I mean, if he's telling the truth,
then he has no reason--

19:24.581 --> 19:26.333
That was his recommendation.

19:27.125 --> 19:28.669
I'm going to have to ask you to leave.

19:29.336 --> 19:30.546
Tyler...

19:31.588 --> 19:33.632
you're about to be buried in legal fees.

19:33.632 --> 19:38.178
Your parents are about
to be buried in legal fees.

19:38.178 --> 19:39.721
That's my son you're talking about.

19:39.721 --> 19:42.099
You cannot afford

19:42.099 --> 19:44.017
what is about to come at you.

19:45.269 --> 19:46.937
- Is it worth it?
- Get out.

19:48.272 --> 19:49.356
You'll be hearing from me.

20:08.125 --> 20:09.209
- Do you--

20:11.420 --> 20:13.463
Do you wish Elizabeth was related to you

20:14.715 --> 20:16.008
instead of me?

20:16.008 --> 20:18.510
Stop feeling sorry for yourself.

20:18.510 --> 20:20.971
- She lied to you about the documents
she wanted me to sign.

20:21.680 --> 20:23.140
She lies.

20:23.140 --> 20:24.558
That's who she is.

20:24.558 --> 20:26.894
Why can't you just admit
that you were wrong about her?

20:27.394 --> 20:30.397
Because you're this great man
and you never make mistakes?

20:30.397 --> 20:31.565
You're never wrong?

20:35.068 --> 20:36.987
Did you speak to the reporter?

20:44.328 --> 20:45.454
No.

20:46.872 --> 20:49.374
♪

20:50.542 --> 20:52.294
Then I'm choosing to believe you.

20:53.962 --> 20:57.966
♪

20:59.968 --> 21:03.263
- We have a very big announcement
to tell y'all.

21:03.263 --> 21:05.307
- Are you excited?
- Walgreens isn't happy.

21:05.307 --> 21:07.017
Normandy is a disaster zone.

21:07.017 --> 21:09.978
We need new lab directors
and lab managers.

21:09.978 --> 21:12.981
- Because you replaced Mark
with a dermatologist.

21:13.815 --> 21:15.734
- Because I don't want someone
who's going to create problems.

21:15.734 --> 21:18.820
- But we can't keep fighting fires
by creating fires.

21:18.820 --> 21:21.949
We have to focus on
the root cause of the problem.

21:21.949 --> 21:23.742
What is the root cause?

21:24.660 --> 21:26.161
CHRISTIAN HOLMES:
And I think she deserves--

21:26.161 --> 21:27.871
What is the root cause?

21:28.455 --> 21:30.249
So without further ado,

21:30.249 --> 21:32.835
I present to you our fearless leader,

21:32.835 --> 21:34.586
Elizabeth Holmes.

21:48.517 --> 21:52.020
We've got herpes!

21:52.020 --> 21:54.690
♪

21:54.690 --> 21:58.360
:
Theranos! Theranos!

21:58.360 --> 22:00.529
Theranos!

22:00.946 --> 22:02.739
Theranos!

22:02.739 --> 22:04.408
Theranos!

22:04.408 --> 22:05.868
Theranos!

22:06.493 --> 22:08.078
Theranos!

22:08.412 --> 22:09.955
Theranos!

22:10.205 --> 22:11.707
Theranos!

22:12.249 --> 22:13.375
Theranos!

22:18.463 --> 22:21.091
Congratulations on the FDA approval.

22:21.091 --> 22:22.885
ELIZABETH:
Moving in the right direction.

22:22.885 --> 22:24.803
Where are we with the article?

22:25.429 --> 22:27.097
Tyler didn't sign.

22:27.097 --> 22:28.891
It doesn't matter because he's a kid.

22:29.641 --> 22:32.227
And they've lost
more than half of their sources.

22:32.936 --> 22:33.937
Right.

22:34.313 --> 22:38.233
But we need answers to those questions
that the journalist sent.

22:38.233 --> 22:41.069
We need to categorically deny
the allegations.

22:48.702 --> 22:50.204
I won!

22:51.705 --> 22:53.332
Oh, I had an idea last night.

23:02.341 --> 23:03.717
What the fuck?

23:13.227 --> 23:15.312
- Yeah, I know, Richard.
I'm looking at it.

23:15.312 --> 23:16.855
RICHARD FUISZ:
<i>In your own paper!</i>

23:16.855 --> 23:20.442
She, she wrote and published
a brag about herpes

23:20.442 --> 23:21.777
in your own paper?

23:21.777 --> 23:23.779
She's spitting in your face.

23:23.779 --> 23:25.489
How could this happen?

23:25.489 --> 23:26.865
- Well, it's an op-ed, Richard.

23:26.865 --> 23:28.784
Opinion and news are totally separate.

23:28.784 --> 23:29.785
They don't know what we're working on.

23:29.785 --> 23:31.245
I'll tell you how it happened.

23:31.745 --> 23:34.373
Guess who's the new investor in Theranos?

23:34.373 --> 23:36.041
Rupert Murdoch!

23:36.041 --> 23:38.418
Rupert fucking Murdoch.

23:38.418 --> 23:40.295
The man who owns your paper.

23:40.295 --> 23:42.464
<i>I just found out this morning.</i>

23:42.464 --> 23:44.091
Um, I'm sorry.

23:44.091 --> 23:47.386
Where-- where did--
where is this information coming from?

23:47.386 --> 23:49.680
It's coming from, you figure it out.

23:49.680 --> 23:51.598
That's where it's coming from.

23:51.598 --> 23:53.851
$125 million,

23:53.851 --> 23:56.395
the most he's ever invested
in a tech company.

23:57.813 --> 23:59.648
Are you sure about this?

23:59.648 --> 24:02.109
- Your story is dead.
He's going to bury it.

24:02.109 --> 24:04.820
He's going to bury it
to protect his investment.

24:04.820 --> 24:07.447
That's not necessarily true.

24:07.447 --> 24:08.574
<i>The op-ed!</i>

24:09.116 --> 24:10.909
The op-ed!

24:20.419 --> 24:24.631
♪

24:33.473 --> 24:35.267
- The opinion page
has nothing to do--

24:35.267 --> 24:37.811
Murdoch just invested $125 million.

24:39.771 --> 24:40.898
In Theranos?

24:40.898 --> 24:42.399
No, in railroads.

24:42.941 --> 24:43.984
Wow.

24:44.693 --> 24:46.737
- Guess he should have
called you first, huh?

24:46.737 --> 24:49.031
Yeah. Uh, we gotta run the story now.

24:49.573 --> 24:50.908
- We can't run it now.
- Why not?

24:50.908 --> 24:52.326
Because it's not ready.

24:52.326 --> 24:55.037
You've lost half your sources,
so we need more proof.

24:55.037 --> 24:57.372
- We have to wait.
- Judith, come--

24:58.332 --> 24:59.499
Come on.

25:00.751 --> 25:03.587
Obama just named her
global ambassador of something.

25:03.587 --> 25:05.881
The woman is worth
four and a half billion dollars.

25:05.881 --> 25:07.966
They are fucking winning here.

25:07.966 --> 25:10.719
- John, in Sicily, every year--

25:10.719 --> 25:12.012
Why are we talking about Italy?

25:12.012 --> 25:13.722
No, no. We're talking about Sicily.

25:13.722 --> 25:15.849
There's a practice called <i>la mattanza.</i>

25:16.308 --> 25:17.226
Okay.

25:18.519 --> 25:21.980
- The fishermen, they wade
into the Mediterranean Sea.

25:22.898 --> 25:24.149
The water is up to their waist.

25:24.149 --> 25:26.818
They've got their clubs
and spears in hand.

25:27.736 --> 25:28.820
And they stand there.

25:30.072 --> 25:31.156
Very still.

25:31.782 --> 25:32.783
For hours.

25:34.368 --> 25:35.994
Till the fish start to gather around them.

25:37.246 --> 25:40.290
Because the men are so still

25:41.124 --> 25:42.876
and they've waited so long,

25:42.876 --> 25:44.503
the fish don't even realize they're there.

25:44.503 --> 25:46.588
They, they think
they're part of the scenery.

25:47.548 --> 25:48.590
But then...

25:50.092 --> 25:51.802
once there are enough fish gathered,

25:52.761 --> 25:54.263
someone gives the signal.

25:54.263 --> 25:55.389
And then...

25:55.931 --> 25:57.015
bam!

25:57.891 --> 25:58.934
Bam, bam, bam!

25:58.934 --> 26:00.769
Tch tch tch tch tch. Tch tch tch tch.

26:00.769 --> 26:02.563
Bam! Bam!

26:05.440 --> 26:06.567
So you see.

26:07.276 --> 26:08.318
Very vivid imagery.

26:09.194 --> 26:10.195
We wait.

26:12.531 --> 26:14.241
Until Boies responds to my questions?

26:15.659 --> 26:17.244
Until we know we've got them.

26:23.709 --> 26:25.169
- Yup.
- Go on.

26:53.363 --> 26:54.573
- Oh!
- Oh my god!

26:54.573 --> 26:55.657
- I--

26:55.657 --> 26:58.410
- I'm sorry, your roommate,
she just let me in downstairs, and I--

26:58.410 --> 27:00.537
- Wh-what are you,
what are you doing here?

27:01.330 --> 27:03.707
I, uh, brought a lamp.

27:05.626 --> 27:07.961
Yeah, you just, you weren't
answering my calls,

27:07.961 --> 27:12.341
so I thought I would stop by
and say hi and bring a lamp.

27:12.341 --> 27:15.260
Remember you told me
you didn't have one for your room?

27:19.348 --> 27:20.849
How long have you had that knife?

27:20.849 --> 27:22.559
- I, I don't know, it helps the--

27:23.519 --> 27:24.645
it helps me sleep.

27:33.654 --> 27:36.990
When you were at Theranos,
did you ever hear of Ian Gibbons?

27:39.576 --> 27:40.661
Maybe.

27:43.664 --> 27:46.834
- Carreyrou told me that
he was a chemist there.

27:50.045 --> 27:52.673
They were pressuring him so much that, um,

27:55.217 --> 27:56.426
he killed himself.

28:01.557 --> 28:03.433
I keep thinking about him.

28:07.479 --> 28:08.772
Yeah, it's, uh...

28:10.732 --> 28:11.900
It's bad right now.

28:14.403 --> 28:15.988
They're suing me.

28:17.531 --> 28:19.283
My grandfather stopped talking to me.

28:19.283 --> 28:22.452
They're tracking everything I do.

28:33.297 --> 28:35.257
At least now you have an ugly lamp.

29:03.368 --> 29:05.829
David, what are you doing here?

29:05.829 --> 29:06.997
I want to talk.

29:08.290 --> 29:10.792
- Were you in the neighborhood?
- No.

29:12.753 --> 29:15.088
The article is not going away.

29:15.756 --> 29:19.760
It's not moving forward
but it's not going away,

29:19.760 --> 29:24.389
and I can't make it go away
until I know what they have.

29:26.767 --> 29:31.104
This is the moment
where you tell me everything

29:31.104 --> 29:32.731
that you've been hiding from me.

29:32.731 --> 29:37.986
♪

29:41.406 --> 29:44.576
♪

29:44.576 --> 29:47.120
♪

29:53.168 --> 29:55.045
Oh, you need to be prepared.

29:55.045 --> 29:56.255
I'm prepared.

29:57.130 --> 29:59.967
- For, for what?
- For Boies killing your story.

29:59.967 --> 30:01.635
- No.
- He's the one that called the meeting.

30:01.635 --> 30:03.053
I'm sure he has evidence that refutes it.

30:03.053 --> 30:04.346
Judith, the story is good.

30:04.346 --> 30:06.557
I still have Dr. Betz in Arizona.

30:06.557 --> 30:08.058
I've got the nurse, Carmen Washington.

30:08.058 --> 30:10.102
I have that patient.
I have Erika Cheung,

30:10.102 --> 30:12.104
Mark Roessler, Richard Fuisz,

30:12.104 --> 30:14.481
Rochelle Gibbons, Phyllis Gardner--
On background.

30:14.481 --> 30:16.483
- And Tyler.
- You haven't heard from Tyler?

30:16.984 --> 30:19.903
- No. But that also means
I haven't heard that he's recanted.

30:19.903 --> 30:23.407
Come on. Whatever happened
to stab the fish?

30:23.407 --> 30:25.242
- Sometimes the fish
can take you to court.

30:26.743 --> 30:28.161
And then you have to let them go.

30:30.080 --> 30:32.165
So say it back to me,
you have to let the fish go.

30:34.501 --> 30:36.962
- Sometimes you have to let the fish go.
- Exactly.

30:37.754 --> 30:40.757
So thank you for coming by.

30:41.842 --> 30:43.468
This is John Carreyrou

30:43.468 --> 30:46.555
and Jay Conti, the deputy general counsel
of our parent company.

30:46.555 --> 30:47.806
Ah, hold on.

30:48.640 --> 30:51.018
Oh, are we recording?
Is this a deposition?

30:51.018 --> 30:53.437
- Nope. Just want a record.
- Well, hold on.

30:54.062 --> 30:56.231
Maybe we want to record.
What do you, what do you think?

30:56.231 --> 30:57.399
- Yeah, why not? Sure.
- Okay.

30:58.066 --> 31:01.069
So where is the app?

31:01.069 --> 31:03.322
Uh, Recorder Plus.

31:03.697 --> 31:05.782
JUDITH:
Uh-huh. And do I download it?

31:05.782 --> 31:07.784
-Yeah, go to the App Store.
-Mm-hmm.

31:07.784 --> 31:08.994
And how much is it?

31:08.994 --> 31:11.038
- No, it's free.
- Oh, okay, free.

31:11.830 --> 31:14.583
Ah, there it is.

31:14.583 --> 31:16.543
Okay, got it. You got it?

31:16.543 --> 31:17.544
-Got it.
- Got it.

31:17.544 --> 31:19.254
Can we keep moving forward?

31:19.254 --> 31:20.964
Yeah, yeah, yeah, of course, of course.

31:20.964 --> 31:23.759
Okay. So you sent us
80 questions for review,

31:23.759 --> 31:26.386
and we are here to rebut the false premise

31:26.386 --> 31:27.721
embedded in those questions.

31:27.721 --> 31:31.391
Now, it's apparent to us
that one of your key sources

31:31.391 --> 31:33.810
is a young man named Tyler Schultz.

31:33.810 --> 31:36.563
- We aren't disclosing
our confidential sources,

31:36.563 --> 31:38.857
nor should you presume
to know who they are.

31:38.857 --> 31:41.235
Can we move on?
You're absolutely right, Judith.

31:42.110 --> 31:44.738
I'm not asking you
to disclose your sources.

31:44.738 --> 31:47.574
I respect journalists,
and I'm trying to protect you.

31:47.574 --> 31:49.743
There just isn't a story here.

31:49.743 --> 31:51.286
Then answer my questions.

31:55.666 --> 31:56.708
John.

31:57.376 --> 31:58.335
It's John, right?

31:58.335 --> 31:59.628
It is, David.

32:00.629 --> 32:03.423
- You will make a fool
of yourself by printing this.

32:03.423 --> 32:06.009
- Mm-hmm, so you're the good cop, David?

32:06.009 --> 32:08.053
No.

32:09.179 --> 32:10.681
I'm just trying to figure out

32:11.598 --> 32:13.392
how we could have arrived at a place

32:13.392 --> 32:16.812
where <i>The Journal</i> is considering
publication of an article

32:16.812 --> 32:20.065
I know to be false, misleading,

32:20.065 --> 32:21.775
and unfair

32:21.775 --> 32:23.986
and threatens to disclose information

32:23.986 --> 32:27.072
that Theranos rigorously protects

32:27.072 --> 32:29.157
as trade secrets.

32:30.075 --> 32:33.996
Do you really believe
that all the recognition

32:33.996 --> 32:37.624
by the academic, scientific,
and healthcare communities

32:37.624 --> 32:40.794
of Theranos' achievements is wrong?

32:40.794 --> 32:44.381
That every previous published report
about Theranos,

32:44.381 --> 32:46.466
including in <i>The Journal</i> itself,

32:46.466 --> 32:50.512
has been the result
of misleading manipulation

32:50.512 --> 32:51.763
by the company?

32:52.973 --> 32:54.308
Wow.

32:54.808 --> 32:57.144
If it were true, that's a powerful story.

32:58.103 --> 32:59.813
Why would you let a story like that go?

32:59.813 --> 33:02.608
Why would you check it thoroughly?

33:03.483 --> 33:06.570
That would be a career-defining story.

33:08.071 --> 33:09.615
The only problem is

33:11.450 --> 33:13.368
none of it is true.

33:13.368 --> 33:16.288
♪

33:16.288 --> 33:19.041
♪

33:19.041 --> 33:21.460
♪

33:21.460 --> 33:23.295
Then why don't you answer my questions?

33:29.218 --> 33:32.012
I just want to know--
Here's what I want to know, John.

33:32.012 --> 33:34.431
What about your conduct in Arizona?

33:34.431 --> 33:36.725
What you were doing
down there with those doctors

33:36.725 --> 33:39.269
was nothing short of yellow journalism.

33:39.269 --> 33:41.230
- Oh, David, where'd the good cop go?
- Yellow journalism?

33:41.230 --> 33:43.649
- You were asking those doctors
loaded questions.

33:43.649 --> 33:44.733
Okay, here's a loaded question.

33:44.733 --> 33:47.694
If Theranos has new technology,
what is it?

33:47.694 --> 33:49.905
- Okay, so you want us to give you
the formula for Coke

33:49.905 --> 33:51.240
so that we can--

33:51.240 --> 33:52.574
- Nobody's asking
for the formula for Coke.

33:52.574 --> 33:55.410
- By the way, I like Pepsi.
- Okay. Just answer.

33:56.036 --> 33:59.373
Does Theranos use fingerstick samples
in their technology or not?

33:59.373 --> 34:00.499
- That's a trade secret.
Yes or no. Okay.

34:00.499 --> 34:01.500
That is a trade secret.

34:01.500 --> 34:03.627
- How about this?
This is another easy one.

34:03.627 --> 34:06.046
Are you using Siemens machines
in your labs?

34:06.046 --> 34:08.465
Yes, but for comparison purposes only.

34:08.465 --> 34:09.466
So you acknowledge you have them?

34:09.466 --> 34:11.552
For comparison purposes.

34:11.552 --> 34:12.678
- You're grasping at straws--

34:12.678 --> 34:14.638
- She said, for comparison purposes.
Move on.

34:14.638 --> 34:18.183
- Just... walk me through
some of the language

34:18.183 --> 34:19.643
that's been changed recently
on the website.

34:19.643 --> 34:21.311
Oh, language on the website?

34:21.311 --> 34:25.899
- The phrase, "Many of our tests
only require a few drops of blood."

34:25.899 --> 34:27.651
That phrase was recently deleted.

34:27.651 --> 34:29.528
Yes, for marketing accuracy.

34:32.865 --> 34:33.991
Accuracy?

34:34.950 --> 34:37.536
So you characterize
the language before as inaccurate?

34:37.536 --> 34:38.495
Alright.

34:39.121 --> 34:41.874
We will acknowledge
that not every blood test

34:41.874 --> 34:44.376
is run on proprietary technology,

34:44.376 --> 34:47.045
but they're transitioning.

34:47.045 --> 34:49.965
It's a transitional process. A journey.

34:51.592 --> 34:52.759
A journey.

34:55.721 --> 34:57.014
A journey.

34:58.682 --> 35:00.142
Alright. This meeting's over.

35:00.142 --> 35:02.853
- W-- well, it's only been four hours.

35:02.853 --> 35:03.770
I mean--

35:09.651 --> 35:13.614
♪

35:17.159 --> 35:18.785
Oh my god, holy shit.

35:19.953 --> 35:21.872
- They admitted to using
third-party analyzers.

35:21.872 --> 35:22.748
They sure did.

35:22.748 --> 35:25.083
- Yeah. After months of saying
they don't use third-party analyzers.

35:25.083 --> 35:26.668
- They sure did.
- So, Judith...

35:27.794 --> 35:29.588
- is this--
- Bam!

35:39.264 --> 35:41.934
Elizabeth, they're running it.

35:41.934 --> 35:43.602
So when will it come out?

35:44.228 --> 35:46.271
ELIZABETH:
Uh, I don't know. Soon.

35:47.397 --> 35:50.526
I spoke to Rupert and asked him
to kill the story, but, uh--

35:50.526 --> 35:52.361
You asked Rupert Murdoch

35:53.362 --> 35:55.989
to kill a story in
<i>The Wall Street Journal</i> for you?

35:55.989 --> 35:57.449
Of course.

35:57.449 --> 35:58.867
He told me that his hands are tied.

35:59.660 --> 36:03.038
I don't understand why
he can't just make a phone call.

36:03.580 --> 36:04.873
How bad will it be?

36:05.999 --> 36:07.417
Nothing we can't handle.

36:11.338 --> 36:12.506
George...

36:13.298 --> 36:15.843
I want to know that I have your support.

36:18.428 --> 36:19.680
I hear

36:21.682 --> 36:26.728
you're joining the Harvard Medical School
Board of Fellows.

36:27.312 --> 36:30.357
Congratulations. You must be riding high.

36:31.942 --> 36:34.611
- I know! A college dropout
joining the board

36:34.611 --> 36:36.864
of a Harvard Medical School.

36:37.865 --> 36:39.867
Obviously, Harvard's support
of our company

36:39.867 --> 36:42.870
means more to me than a reporter
who doesn't understand.

36:42.870 --> 36:44.246
Elizabeth...

36:45.956 --> 36:47.708
I've worked for two presidents,

36:49.334 --> 36:50.836
Nixon and Reagan,

36:52.546 --> 36:54.214
who made bad decisions.

36:56.091 --> 36:57.509
Nixon, more so.

36:59.011 --> 37:00.137
But Reagan

37:01.930 --> 37:05.017
got mixed up in the Iran-Contra affair,

37:06.852 --> 37:08.729
and it hurt his legacy.

37:09.271 --> 37:10.647
He was a great man.

37:13.317 --> 37:15.527
But he started listening
to the wrong people.

37:16.653 --> 37:20.532
It's easy to make the mistake
of listening to the wrong people.

37:22.242 --> 37:23.785
If mistakes were made...

37:25.704 --> 37:28.373
I think it might be time
to consider whether you have

37:28.373 --> 37:30.083
the right people around you.

37:34.129 --> 37:36.381
If Sunny is the right person.

37:43.805 --> 37:46.725
Baby, how did it go with George?

37:52.064 --> 37:54.274
I said, how did it go with George?

37:55.400 --> 37:57.986
- I have to pack for my Harvard Board
dinner tonight and I don't--

37:57.986 --> 37:59.279
I laid out your clothes.

37:59.279 --> 38:01.073
- Yeah, I don't want to wear
what you picked out.

38:01.073 --> 38:02.366
Just wear it, why don't you?

38:11.500 --> 38:14.378
- I don't know what
I'm supposed to fucking do.

38:14.378 --> 38:15.921
I don't even know
when it's going to come out.

38:15.921 --> 38:17.172
I don't know what it's going to say.

38:18.674 --> 38:20.133
You should have protected me.

38:21.051 --> 38:21.969
Okay.

38:22.511 --> 38:23.554
I see.

38:25.097 --> 38:26.515
George told you to blame me.

38:28.642 --> 38:30.602
That's what you're going to do?
You're going to blame me?

38:30.602 --> 38:31.687
No.

38:32.396 --> 38:33.814
Of course not.

38:35.232 --> 38:37.150
I have to meet the jet.

38:43.574 --> 38:45.701
Because I know everything that you know.

38:45.701 --> 38:47.661
- What?

38:49.913 --> 38:51.874
- You were on all of those e-mails.

39:02.009 --> 39:03.218
Well, I'm the CEO.

39:05.012 --> 39:07.222
And I don't always read all of my e-mails.

39:15.063 --> 39:16.398
I love you, Tiger.

39:19.401 --> 39:20.986
I miss you already.

39:22.946 --> 39:23.989
Miss you too.

39:36.502 --> 39:38.212
- Richard.
<i>They killed it.</i>

39:38.212 --> 39:39.546
<i>It's dead.</i>

39:40.714 --> 39:42.007
You fucked it up.

39:43.008 --> 39:44.593
I knew it.

39:44.593 --> 39:47.054
You got cocky and you fucked it up.

39:47.054 --> 39:49.181
<i>I'm taking it somewhere else.</i>

39:49.181 --> 39:51.266
It's too late for that.

39:51.266 --> 39:54.102
- Oh, is that right?
Is that what you think?

39:54.102 --> 39:56.772
Hah. No way, buddy. No way!

39:56.772 --> 39:59.733
It's running tonight, buddy.

40:01.026 --> 40:03.403
- Tonight? What? The--
<i>Mm-hmm.</i>

40:04.029 --> 40:05.197
<i>Really?</i>

40:06.365 --> 40:07.491
Yes!

40:07.908 --> 40:09.409
That's, uh, good.

40:10.327 --> 40:12.454
That's good. You, you got it done.

40:13.580 --> 40:14.706
Yeah, well, you're welcome.

40:14.706 --> 40:16.917
Oh, what, am I supposed to thank you?

40:16.917 --> 40:18.669
I gave it to you on a plate.

40:19.962 --> 40:21.839
